The Kwara State Governor, Abdulfatah Ahmed, has approved February 15th and March 1st, respectively, as work-free days for Kwara State public servants.
This, the Governor said, is to allow public servants to exercise their franchise during the forthcoming general elections scheduled for Feb.16th and March 2nd, 2019.
The governor in a statement by the Kwara State Head of Service, Susan Oluwole, said Public servants are, therefore, advised to conduct themselves in a manner devoid of any acrimony.
Work resumes on Monday, 18 February and Monday, 4 March 2019, respectively.
